, and for FRI and FRII\nsources an orientation-based unification and beaming model is used to partition\nflux between the core and extended lobes and hotspots. The simulation output\ncan be post-processed to achieve more complete agreement with observational\ndata in the years ahead, with the aim of using these 'idealised skies' in\ntelescope simulators to optimise the design of the SKA itself (abridged).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 22 May 2008 09:14:35 GMT"}],"update_date":"2010-11-09"}
